Christy was based on the novel Christy by Catherine Marshall, the widow of Senate chaplain Peter Marshall. The novel had been a bestseller in 1968, and the week following the debut of the TV-movie and program saw the novel jump from #120 up to #15 on the USA Today bestseller list. Series regular Tyne Daly won an Emmy Award for her work on the series.', NULL, NULL, 1.3609, 8.375, 0, 1.0, '2026-07-20 01:02:04', '2026-07-20 01:02:04');
